# NestJS Error Handling

- **Use built-in HTTP exceptions:** Throw `NotFoundException`, `BadRequestException`, `UnauthorizedException`, etc. — never throw a raw `Error`.
- **Global exception filter:** Register a global filter in `main.ts` to catch unhandled errors and return a consistent JSON error shape.
- **No swallowed errors:** Every `catch` block must either re-throw or log with context. Never silently ignore exceptions.

```ts
// ❌ BAD
throw new Error('Not found');

// ✅ GOOD
import { NotFoundException } from '@nestjs/common';
throw new NotFoundException(`User with id ${id} not found`);
```

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — consistent error shape via global filter
@Catch()
export class AllExceptionsFilter implements ExceptionFilter {
  catch(exception: unknown, host: ArgumentsHost) {
    const status =
      exception instanceof HttpException
        ? exception.getStatus()
        : HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR;
    // ... return standardised JSON
  }
}
```
